hern Ireland and India. The book makes a timely intervention, foregrounding the value of creativity for those who are commonly marginalised from centres of power, including from the mainstream cultural industries. The authors also critically reflect on the possibilities and limitations of collaborative research within and beyond the academy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aarts and creative practice.  acoloniality.  acreativity.  ahostile environment.  alived theory.  aparticipatory research.  arace and racism.  aradical capitalism.  aradical openness.  aresistance.1 aBidisha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoutinho, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGearing, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHargey, Fionntán, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasan-Bounds, Daisy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaganathan, Aditi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLynch, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahn, Churnjeet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMahn, Churnjeet, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMalik, Sarita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalik, Sarita, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMurphy, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPierse, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPierse, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRao KV, Raghavendra, econtributor.4ctb4